- My dad.

37:06.800 --> 37:08.711
So tell me, Goof,

37:08.840 --> 37:11.070
is that kid of yours
still givin' you guff?

37:11.200 --> 37:12.997
Oh, I don't know
what's wrong.

37:13.120 --> 37:16.999
Just seems like everything I try
only drives Max further away.

37:17.120 --> 37:19.395
Maybe I oughta just back off.
I don't know.

37:19.520 --> 37:21.317
Wrong, Goof.

37:21.440 --> 37:24.238
Look, if you keep 'em
under your thumb,

37:24.360 --> 37:27.670
they'll never end up
in the gutter.

37:32.920 --> 37:35.036
Too bad, Pete.
Almost.

37:35.160 --> 37:38.277
Almost? Hah!
Watch this.

37:38.400 --> 37:39.913
P.J.!

37:40.040 --> 37:42.429
Here, sir. Comin', sir. Yes, sir.

37:47.400 --> 37:49.231
Whoo-hoo!
Strike-ola!

37:49.360 --> 37:51.590
Yee-haw! Thank you.
Thank you. Yes!

37:51.720 --> 37:54.075
And the crowd goes wild!
Ahh-ha-ha-ha!

37:54.200 --> 37:56.555
High five, son!
Psych!

37:56.680 --> 37:58.716
Ha-ha-ha-ha!

37:58.840 --> 38:01.513
Say, Goof, why don't
you two stay for dinner?

38:01.640 --> 38:03.790
- Cool!
- Oh, no thanks, Pete.

38:03.920 --> 38:06.673
- Max and I have some fish to catch.
- Dad, we can do that tomorrow.

38:06.800 --> 38:08.791
So, uh,
what're we havin'?

38:08.920 --> 38:12.754
- But, Max, I thought...
- A-A-Ahem! Under your thumb, Goof.

38:15.160 --> 38:16.434
- Maximilian!
- What?

38:16.560 --> 38:20.519
Get your gear, little man.
We're goin' fishin'!

38:21.720 --> 38:23.790
And I mean now!

38:31.080 --> 38:34.038
Dad, I don't even know
how to fish.

38:34.120 --> 38:36.350
Oh, now come on.
That never stopped me!

38:36.480 --> 38:38.630
Let me show you
a little family secret...

38:38.760 --> 38:41.752
handed down through about
12 or 13 Goof generations.

38:41.880 --> 38:45.998
- The perfect cast!
- The perfect what?

38:46.120 --> 38:50.033
The perfect cast. My dad taught it
to me when I was about your age.

38:50.160 --> 38:53.072
Okay now, watch carefully.

38:53.200 --> 38:55.475
You gotta be l-l-loose.

38:55.600 --> 38:58.558
Relaxed...
with your feet apart.

38:58.680 --> 39:01.956
And... 10:00,
2:00.

39:02.080 --> 39:04.355
Quarter to 3:00.
Tour jete.

39:04.480 --> 39:06.596
Twist. Over.
Pas de deux.

39:06.720 --> 39:08.790
# I'm a little teapot #
And the windup!

39:12.600 --> 39:15.114
And let her fly!

39:15.240 --> 39:17.231
The perfect cast.

39:30.960 --> 39:33.918
And now we reel her in.

39:48.240 --> 39:51.277
Quick,
get the camera!

39:55.280 --> 39:59.114
Must be over three pounds.
I don't wanna miss this!

40:01.440 --> 40:03.192
Look, Max!

40:03.320 --> 40:05.151
A... duh, duh, Dad?

40:05.280 --> 40:07.430
It's Bigfoot!

40:07.560 --> 40:10.870
Could you back up a bit, Mr Foot?
You're out of focus.

40:13.000 --> 40:15.309
What's the idea?

40:17.240 --> 40:19.754
Bigfoot!

40:23.120 --> 40:25.475
Behold
the legendary Bigfoot!

40:25.600 --> 40:28.512
Fabled, but seldom...
Yeow-hoo-hoo!

40:28.640 --> 40:31.871
- It's locked!
- Quick! The sunroof!

40:34.040 --> 40:35.359
Hurry up!

40:38.120 --> 40:39.599
Hurry up!

40:47.080 --> 40:50.470
I can't believe it!
Bigfoot!

40:50.600 --> 40:53.068
And I got
the only video!

40:53.200 --> 40:55.350
We're gonna be famous!

40:57.280 --> 41:00.033
Huh? Grrr.

41:00.160 --> 41:02.799
Let's just get outta here.

41:25.080 --> 41:27.355
Is he gone yet?

41:36.360 --> 41:39.591
Nope. He's still here.

41:44.520 --> 41:49.036
- Gee, Max, was that Bigfoot
or your stomach?

41:49.160 --> 41:52.277
Man, I'm starving.

41:52.400 --> 41:55.437
Alphabet soup comin' up.

42:00.520 --> 42:01.919
Uh, Dad?

42:03.480 --> 42:05.471
Dad!

42:05.600 --> 42:08.068
Stop playing around!
He's coming!

42:12.280 --> 42:17.035
Music!

42:17.160 --> 42:21.836
# You can tell by the way
I use my walk I'm a woman's man #

42:21.960 --> 42:24.997
# No time to talk #

42:25.120 --> 42:27.236
# I've been kicked around
since I was born #

42:27.360 --> 42:30.591
# But then it's all right
It's okay #

42:30.720 --> 42:33.473
Well, it's nice to know
this thing's good for somethin'.

42:37.800 --> 42:41.952
#Stayin' alive, stayin' alive #

42:42.080 --> 42:44.799
#Stayin' alive #

42:52.760 --> 42:54.398
What's so funny?

42:54.520 --> 42:56.590
"Hi, Dad" soup.

42:58.160 --> 43:00.674
Don't tell me you don't remember
"Hi, Dad" soup!

43:01.960 --> 43:04.030
Oh, come on.
Sure you do!

43:04.160 --> 43:07.789
You used to spell things out
using the letters, like, uh, "Hi, Dad,"

43:07.920 --> 43:09.672
- or Maxie, or...
- Ambidextrous?

43:09.800 --> 43:11.358
Yeah! That's...
Huh?

43:11.480 --> 43:13.630
No!
Little words like...

43:13.760 --> 43:16.035
- Hasta la vista?
- Like bye-bye.

43:16.160 --> 43:19.948
- Or "I pledge allegiance"...
- Ayuk-ayuk. Or "I love you"...

43:24.520 --> 43:26.829
Is, uh...
is it soup yet?

43:26.960 --> 43:29.838
Oh, oh.
I almost forgot.

43:29.960 --> 43:31.837
Whoa!
Where'd you learn to do that?

43:31.960 --> 43:35.191
Your granddad taught me that
when we went to Yosemite.

43:35.320 --> 43:37.629
You two did a lot together,
huh?

43:37.760 --> 43:39.079
Yep.

43:40.720 --> 43:43.075
- Max, you and I...
- Dad, I'm sorry...

43:43.200 --> 43:46.476
Um, um...
how's the soup?

43:47.560 --> 43:49.471
Not bad.
Um, not... Ahem.

43:51.800 --> 43:54.314
- What?
- N-nothin'.

44:01.760 --> 44:04.638
Well, we might as well
get some shuteye.

44:04.760 --> 44:06.591
I don't think we're goin'
anywhere tonight.

44:26.320 --> 44:29.118
Hi, Maxie.

45:04.520 --> 45:06.476
"Dear Roxanne,

45:06.600 --> 45:08.636
I couldn't sleep...

45:08.760 --> 45:11.320
so I thought I'd drop you
a line.

45:11.440 --> 45:14.432
Dad and I are having a great time!
We're only days away from L. A...

45:14.560 --> 45:18.155
and I can hardly wait
for the big concert."

45:18.280 --> 45:20.191
Ahh.

45:20.320 --> 45:23.198
More "Hi, Dad" soup, please.

45:29.480 --> 45:33.314
"Dear Roxanne,
sorry I lied,

45:33.440 --> 45:35.954
but I'm not really going
to the Powerline concert.

45:36.080 --> 45:39.311
You may never want
to see me again..."

45:39.440 --> 45:43.274
Oh, man!
I'm dead no matter what I do!

46:38.720 --> 46:41.917
How many cups of sugar does it take
to get to the moon?

46:42.040 --> 46:45.510
Ah... three and a half?

47:17.880 --> 47:20.553
- Pickup.
- Hold your horses.

47:24.800 --> 47:26.836
- Short stack?
- Right here.

47:26.960 --> 47:28.552
Here you go, hun.
Eggs?

47:28.680 --> 47:30.636
Eggs?

47:30.760 --> 47:32.876
- Eggs!
- Uh-oh, yeah, yeah. Right here. Sorry.

47:33.000 --> 47:35.116
Here you go, cutie.

47:51.760 --> 47:56.072
- Max, I think we need
to talk about this.
- Huh?

47:56.200 --> 48:00.079
Seems to me you need to start
taking some responsibility around here.

48:00.200 --> 48:03.272
Excuse me. Can I have
your attention, please?

48:03.400 --> 48:04.719
A- A-Ahem!

48:04.840 --> 48:08.833
I, Goofy, hereby dub my son
Maximilian...

48:08.960 --> 48:13.988
Official Navigator and Head
"Which-Wayer" of this here road trip.

48:14.120 --> 48:16.554
- Isn't that nice?
- Hee-haw!

48:16.680 --> 48:20.753
- Seriously?
- I'm not even lookin'
at the map any more.

48:20.880 --> 48:24.509
As a matter of fact, you can pick all
the stops from here to Lake Destiny.

48:24.640 --> 48:27.757
I trust you wholeheartedly,
son.

48:27.880 --> 48:30.314
To the open road!

48:30.440 --> 48:32.556
To the... open road!

49:16.200 --> 49:17.633
Oh boy!

50:16.080 --> 50:17.911
Gosh!

50:20.880 --> 50:24.236
Check out the bed!

50:24.360 --> 50:26.954
Check out the dresser!
Coral!

50:27.080 --> 50:29.355
Nice lamp.

50:29.480 --> 50:31.710
Classy choice there,
navigator.

50:31.840 --> 50:33.751
This is the police!

50:33.880 --> 50:37.759
We've got the place surrounded, see?
You Goofs come out with your hands up.

50:41.320 --> 50:44.551
You should've seen
the look on your face!

50:44.780 --> 50:47.638
- You really
had him fooled, Pete!
- Me?

50:47.760 --> 50:49.830
You jumped outta
your skin!

50:49.960 --> 50:52.315
I was just pretendin' for your sake.
- All right, sure!

50:52.440 --> 50:54.510
- Did too!
- Did not!

50:54.640 --> 50:57.677
Oh, ain't this sweet?

50:57.800 --> 51:02.999
Don't let him fool you with that
buddy-buddy act now. Under your thumb!

51:03.120 --> 51:07.033
So... since we're all bein'
palsy-walsy here,

51:07.160 --> 51:09.196
- how 'bout lettin' me hook up the R.V.
- Well...

51:09.320 --> 51:13.108
- Oh, it's just a little tiny extension
cord. You'll hardly even notice it.
- Okay.

51:13.240 --> 51:14.753
Great!
P.J.!

51:19.560 --> 51:24.031
Hey, Goof, why don't you order
us a pizza? This might take a while.

51:26.920 --> 51:30.833
- No, I mean it... Ahh!
- Here you go, kids.
I'm gonna check out the hot tub.

51:30.960 --> 51:32.757
- Okay, sir.
- All right.

51:32.880 --> 51:34.711
I can't believe you, man.

51:34.840 --> 51:37.877
Whatever made you think your dad
would fall for a stupid idea like that?

51:38.000 --> 51:40.230
- It wasn't stupid!
- Come on! It was really stupid.

51:40.360 --> 51:42.396
Changing the map?

51:42.520 --> 51:46.308
I didn't know what I was doin',
all right? I-I was panicked.

51:49.800 --> 51:54.237
Oof-oof-oof.
Oh-oh-ah-ah!

51:54.360 --> 51:56.920
Ahh!

52:03.240 --> 52:06.755
Taking a break from
the M.T.V. Generation, huh?

52:06.880 --> 52:09.348
Can't say as I blame ya.

52:09.480 --> 52:12.199
People are always puttin'
too much water in these things.

52:12.320 --> 52:14.470
So, um...

52:14.600 --> 52:18.229
you and your son seem to be, uh,
gettin' along just hunky-dory, huh?

52:18.360 --> 52:20.430
Yeah!
It's been great!

52:20.560 --> 52:23.120
You know, it's funny, but none
of your techniques worked for me.

52:23.240 --> 52:25.959
The harder I tried,
the worse it got.

52:26.080 --> 52:29.789
- Once I eased up, things just clicked!
- Oh, that's swell.

52:29.920 --> 52:32.992
So, there's
no problems then, huh?

52:33.120 --> 52:34.917
Not a one!

52:37.000 --> 52:40.675
That's uh...
I just hate to be...

52:40.800 --> 52:43.997
- the bearer of bad news, but uh...
- What is it, Pete?

52:44.120 --> 52:48.159
- Your kid's dupin' ya.
- What do you mean?

52:48.280 --> 52:51.113
Well, I heard the little mutant tellin'
P.J. That he changed the map,

52:51.240 --> 52:53.993
so you're headin' straight
to L.A., pal.

52:54.120 --> 52:57.396
- What?
- Ahh, you tried, Goof.

52:57.520 --> 53:02.230
- He's just a bad kid, that's all.
- I don't believe you.

53:02.360 --> 53:04.749
- What?
- I don't believe ya, Pete!

53:04.880 --> 53:08.031
Well hey, don't take my word for it.
Check your map.

53:08.160 --> 53:12.790
I don't need to check the map.
I trust my son.

53:12.920 --> 53:16.754
You know, maybe Max isn't all the things
that you think a son should be.

53:16.880 --> 53:18.871
But... he loves me.

53:19.000 --> 53:21.309
Hey, my son respects me!

53:21.440 --> 53:23.590
Yeah.

53:25.320 --> 53:27.914
Check the map, Goof!

54:00.040 --> 54:02.315
Hi, Dad.

54:04.360 --> 54:07.909
Sorry about the mess.
I- I'll clean it up.

54:18.280 --> 54:20.874
- Me think I better go.
- See ya, Peej.

54:21.000 --> 54:25.073
- Don't forget... Powerline!
- Shh!

54:59.720 --> 55:02.951
Well, here you go,
navigator.

55:03.080 --> 55:05.833
Just follow my route
on the map, son.

55:07.080 --> 55:08.718
Okay.

55:12.600 --> 55:14.591
Here comes our junction.

55:17.800 --> 55:20.360
Okay, Max, now this is it.
Left or right?

55:20.480 --> 55:21.993
Uh...

55:24.320 --> 55:25.878
Come on, Max!

55:26.000 --> 55:27.991
Uh, l-left!

55:40.600 --> 55:44.673
Uh... how 'bout
a song, Dad?

55:44.800 --> 55:48.190
Uh... a game? A game. Yeah!
Yeah, a game. Okay.

55:48.320 --> 55:51.551
Uh...
a man or woman?

55:51.680 --> 55:53.989
A man? Man, okay.
Uh... Walt Disney!

56:18.640 --> 56:22.155
Dad... listen,
about my directions...

56:22.280 --> 56:25.078
Will you listen to me?
I gotta tell you somethin', Dad.

56:25.200 --> 56:28.795
Why bother? I'm probably too stupid
to understand anyway.

56:28.920 --> 56:30.592
Right?

56:30.720 --> 56:33.632
Ahh, forget it.

56:46.800 --> 56:48.677
H- H-Hey, the car!

56:48.800 --> 56:51.314
- What? Now you want to drive too?
- No, Dad.

56:51.440 --> 56:52.998
The car! Look!

56:53.120 --> 56:55.111
The car!

56:58.680 --> 57:01.911
- What'd you do now, Max?
- I didn't do anything, Dad.
I only touched it.

57:04.000 --> 57:06.309
W- W-Whoa!

57:09.880 --> 57:12.075
You locked it!

57:12.200 --> 57:15.795
I locked it? It's your door.
You locked it.

57:15.920 --> 57:18.718
Well, you distracted me.
Whoa!

57:18.840 --> 57:21.832
You should've put the brake on.

57:21.960 --> 57:23.791
Why don't you just
put it on yourself?

57:23.920 --> 57:26.309
See?
You ruin everything.

57:28.320 --> 57:31.471
W- well, y-you r-ruined
the vacation.

57:31.600 --> 57:34.034
I ruined it?

57:34.160 --> 57:38.233
- I never... wanted to go...
on this stupid...

57:38.360 --> 57:41.636
vacationnnnnn!

57:49.600 --> 57:51.670
Ahh! Ahh!

57:51.800 --> 57:54.758
- Now look where you've got us, Dad!
- Where I got us?

57:54.880 --> 57:57.075
- You should've let me stay at home.
- Why?

57:57.200 --> 57:59.236
So you'd end up
in prison?

57:59.360 --> 58:02.318
Prison?
What are you talkin' about?

58:02.440 --> 58:05.432
- Your principal called me.
- It's not what you think.

58:05.560 --> 58:07.357
You even lied to me!

58:07.480 --> 58:09.630
I had to!
You were ruining my life.

58:09.760 --> 58:13.070
I was only tryin'
to take my boy fishin', okay?

58:13.200 --> 58:15.794
I'm not your little boy
any more, Dad!

58:15.920 --> 58:18.878
I've grown up.
I've got my own life now.

58:19.000 --> 58:22.754
I know that!
I just wanted to be part of it.

58:26.480 --> 58:29.711
You're my son, Max.
No matter how big you get,

58:29.840 --> 58:32.479
you'll always be my son.

59:19.400 --> 59:23.712
# There are times you drive me,
shall we say, bananas #

59:23.840 --> 59:28.630
- # And your mind is missin',
no offence, a screw #
- None taken.

59:28.760 --> 59:31.035
# Still whatever mess
I land in #

59:31.160 --> 59:33.799
# Who is
always understandin' #

59:33.920 --> 59:37.151
# Nobody else but you #

59:37.280 --> 59:42.912
# Oh, your moodiness is
now and then bewilderin' #

59:43.040 --> 59:45.998
# And your values may be,
so to speak, askew #

59:46.120 --> 59:47.394
- Gesundheit.
- Thanks.

59:47.520 --> 59:50.193
# Who deserves
a hero's trophy #

59:50.320 --> 59:52.390
# As we face
each "catastro-phee" #

59:52.520 --> 59:57.469
# Nobody else but you #

59:57.600 --> 01:00:01.752
# Nobody else but you #

01:00:01.880 --> 01:00:03.677
# It's just our luck #

01:00:03.800 --> 01:00:06.837
# We're stuck together #

01:00:06.960 --> 01:00:11.715
# Nobody else but you #

01:00:11.840 --> 01:00:17.676
# Is crazy enough to believe
we'll come through #

01:00:17.800 --> 01:00:22.749
# So your jokes are all,
let's face it, prehistoric #

01:00:22.880 --> 01:00:27.396
# And your music sounds
like monkeys in a zoo #

01:00:27.520 --> 01:00:29.954
# But when life
becomes distressin' #

01:00:30.080 --> 01:00:32.150
# Who will I be S.O. Sin' #

01:00:32.280 --> 01:00:36.671
# If you're havin' trouble
guessing, here's a clue #

01:00:36.800 --> 01:00:39.268
# Though he seems
intoxicated #

01:00:39.400 --> 01:00:41.709
# He's just
highly animated #

01:00:41.840 --> 01:00:44.513
# And he's nobody else
but #

01:00:44.640 --> 01:00:48.269
# Nobody else but you #

01:00:48.400 --> 01:00:51.472
# We've turned into #

01:00:51.600 --> 01:00:53.955
# A true-blue duo #

01:00:54.080 --> 01:00:58.039
# Hard times
we've had a few #

01:00:58.160 --> 01:01:00.196
# Like we're
thrown in the drink #

01:01:00.320 --> 01:01:02.515
# Like we're
tossed out of town #

01:01:02.640 --> 01:01:04.870
# But when I start
to sink #

01:01:05.000 --> 01:01:07.753
# Hey, I'd rather go down #

01:01:07.880 --> 01:01:09.677
# With nobody else #

01:01:09.800 --> 01:01:14.874
# But Y-O-U ##

01:01:15.000 --> 01:01:18.151
Aw, Dad!

01:01:21.560 --> 01:01:23.790
Anyway, I figure she's never
gonna want to talk to me again,

01:01:23.880 --> 01:01:25.996
much less go out with me.

01:01:26.120 --> 01:01:28.714
- What a dumb lie, huh?
- What do you know?

01:01:28.840 --> 01:01:31.673
My Maxie... in love.

01:01:31.800 --> 01:01:34.189
Gosh, you're really
growin' up.

01:01:34.320 --> 01:01:39.758
It happened so fast...
I guess I sort of missed it.

01:01:39.880 --> 01:01:42.474
Well, I think the only thing
for us to do now...

01:01:42.600 --> 01:01:45.114
is to get you up onstage
with this Powerline feller.

01:01:45.240 --> 01:01:48.277
Uh, how are we gonna do that?

01:01:48.400 --> 01:01:51.437
- Well, you just leave that up to me.
- No, Dad, really,

01:01:51.560 --> 01:01:53.676
I- I think we should just,
you know, forget it.

01:01:53.800 --> 01:01:57.156
Now how come you always think I'm gonna
lead you into some sort of calamity?

01:01:57.280 --> 01:01:59.077
Uh, uh, Dad? Dad?

01:01:59.200 --> 01:02:01.634
- What's wrong now?
- Look!

01:02:04.000 --> 01:02:05.991
A waterfall!

01:02:06.120 --> 01:02:07.917
Waterfall!

01:02:17.800 --> 01:02:19.756
Dad!

01:02:19.880 --> 01:02:21.836
Max!

01:02:35.440 --> 01:02:37.670
Grab ahold, Max!

01:02:41.840 --> 01:02:44.274
No!

01:02:44.400 --> 01:02:46.152
No!

01:03:04.760 --> 01:03:06.478
Dad!

01:03:18.760 --> 01:03:22.230
10:00, 2:00, quarter to three.
Tour jete.

01:03:22.360 --> 01:03:24.396
Twist. # I'm a little teapot #
Let her fly!

01:03:53.240 --> 01:03:55.117
The perfect cast.

01:04:11.520 --> 01:04:14.318
Boy, this has been
one crazy vacation.

01:04:14.440 --> 01:04:16.237
And it's not over yet!

01:04:34.920 --> 01:04:38.629
- Dad.
- Oof. We made it!

01:04:38.760 --> 01:04:40.830
Come on, Max.
Let's get you onstage.

01:04:40.960 --> 01:04:45.192
- Maybe this isn't such a good idea.
- # Yeah, yeah #

01:04:45.320 --> 01:04:47.390
Ooh, then again...

01:04:47.520 --> 01:04:49.511
Dad? Dad!

01:04:49.640 --> 01:04:52.757
# Hey yeah #

01:04:57.400 --> 01:04:59.595
# I got myself
a notion #

01:05:01.160 --> 01:05:04.038
# One I know
that you'll understand #

01:05:04.160 --> 01:05:07.914
# We set the world
in motion #

01:05:08.040 --> 01:05:11.350
# By reaching out
for each other's hand #

01:05:11.480 --> 01:05:13.198
- Dad?
- # Maybe we'll discover #

01:05:13.320 --> 01:05:15.709
# What we should
have known all along #

01:05:15.840 --> 01:05:18.434
- What are you doin' here? Hey!
- # Yeah #

01:05:18.560 --> 01:05:21.028
- Max? Max?
- # One way or another #

01:05:21.160 --> 01:05:23.276
# Together's where we both belong #

01:05:23.400 --> 01:05:27.359
# If we listen
to each other's heart #

01:05:27.480 --> 01:05:30.233
# We'll find
we're never too far apart #

01:05:30.360 --> 01:05:33.875
# And maybe love
is the reason why #

